\frac{3}{13}
P(W_1) = \frac{32}{52} = \frac{8}{13}, P(W_2)=\frac{20}{52}=\frac{5}{13}
P(S\cap W_2)=\tfrac{3}{13}
P(S \mid W_2) = \frac{P(S \cap W_2)}{P(W_2)} = \frac{3}{13}\times\frac{13}{5} = \frac{3}{5} 
\therefore P(P \mid W_2) = 1-P(S \mid W_2) = \frac{2}{5} 
P(S) = P(S \mid W_1)P(W_1)+P(S\cap W_2) = \frac{14}{32}\times \frac{8}{13}+\frac{3}{13} = \frac{13}{26} = \frac{1}{2} 
P(P) = 1-P(S) = \frac{1}{2} 
\frac{3}{13}=\frac{12}{52}
